substep.action:
For each entry in {{missing_infrastructure}} from Step 2:
1. Resolve source path: the bundled reference inside agent-creator - baselines/* → references/baselines/{filename} - shared-fragments/* → references/shared-fragments/{filename}
2. Resolve destination path: the project's shared/ location - baselines → .vera/shared/baseline/{filename} - shared-fragments → .vera/shared/{filename}
3. Ensure destination directory exists: mkdir -p .vera/shared/baseline (for baselines) mkdir -p .vera/shared (for shared-fragments)
4. Copy: cp {agent-creator-path}/references/baselines/X.md .vera/shared/baseline/X.md cp {agent-creator-path}/references/shared-fragments/X.md .vera/shared/X.md
After copy, verify the file is at its expected path. If a file already exists at the destination, DO NOT overwrite — log a notice and skip. The user's project file is authoritative.
